This paper deals with topology inference over networked dynamical systems, which involves concepts from control theory, machine learning, and information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the analysis, design, and control of complex systems. 

The paper also involves learning and inference, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The paper deals with dynamical systems, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category cs.DS (Dynamical Systems). 

The paper involves information theory concepts such as graph learning, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category cs.IT (Information Theory). 

Finally, the paper deals with nonlinear systems, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which deals with the study of nonlinear systems and their applications to machine learning and optimization.
